description:
Set 1

Promised Land, Sugaree, The Race is On, You Ain't Woman Enough, Bird Song, Mexicali Blues, They Love Each Other, Jack Straw, Stella Blue, Big River, Casey Jones

Set 2

Around & Around, Mississippi Half Step, Me & My Uncle, Row Jimmy, Dark Star-> El Paso-> Eyes Of The World-> Morning Dew, Sugar Magnolia; E: Goin' Down The Road Feeling Bad > One More Saturday Night

Other artist(s): The Band

reviews.review_text: Personal Favorite Show-Thanks Monte Thanks Monte for this fine recording of my favorite show. After standing transfixed for over an hour melting before Dark Star>El Paso>Eyes>Dew my mind was blown and I began to level off at about 100,000 feet and cruised smoothly until the last note was played. Back through the tunnel into Manhattan than crossing 59th st. Bridge into Queens landing at the schoolyard beer and reefers till dawn. Very powerful show -rode it's wake until sunrise. I enjoy the board of this show as well but this recording you can hear the music hit you from all directions. WOS growing with each tour and by summer of 73'it was about eight mos. away from the final draft.I believe One can appreciate the WOS better with audience recordings-really hearing what that thing could do

Mixed show, mixed qualities, mixed feelings This is never one of the clearer, more distinct recordings of this show, not recommended for even the best car stereos. Also, the first set is nothing to shout about. It does sound nice & warm, however, and the second set is a gem if you can hear it right.
